OL,6,FShe found him unconscious and called
OL,7,Ffor assistance from the victim's
OL,8,Ffather and brother who also lived in
OL,9,Fthe house.JMr Conville was first moved
OL,10,Fto a bench and was described as being
OL,11,F"completely unresponsive". He was
OL,12,Flater moved inside the house and was
OL,13,Fheard to be "snoring and shaking".
OL,14,FPolice and an ambulance were called
OL,15,Fand Mr Conville was conveyed to the
OL,16,FRHV where it was established that he
OL,17,Fhad a history of seizures.JHe was
OL,18,Ftreated for a traumatic brain injury
OL,19,Fbut sadly died three days later on May
OL,20,F30, 2022.JA postmortem concluded that
OL,21,FMr Conville had died from a "severe
OL,22,Fhead injury... entirely consistent
OL,23,Fwith the deceased's head striking a
OL,24,Fhard surface such as a wall or the
OL,25,Fground''.
