OL,7,FConville had sustained blunt injuries
OL,8,Fto his face, bruising to the chin and
OL,9,Fscalp along with lacerations.JThe
OL,10,Fpathologist found no fractures to the
OL,11,Fbody and was of the view the injuries
OL,12,Fsustained were caused by "no more than
OL,13,Fmild to moderate force".JA toxicology
OL,14,Freport found alcohol in the deceased's
OL,15,Fblood system along with traces of
OL,16,Fcannabis.JKelly was later arrested and
OL,17,Fduring police interviews he said he
OL,18,Fbelieved he had struck his friend with
OL,19,Fthree blows.JAfter the assault, Mr
OL,20,FConville fell and hit his head on a
OL,21,Ffirm surface and Kelly described
OL,22,Fseeing him "bouncing off a wall''.JHe
OL,23,Faccepted that he assaulted Mr Conville
OL,24,Fbut claimed he had acted in self
OL,25,Fdefence. He said the deceased's
OL,26,Fgirlfriend "was jokingly teasing him
