OL,6,FFollowing sentencing today Detective
OL,7,FChief Inspector Neil McGuinness said:
OL,8,F"The assault took place outside an
OL,9,Faddress in Abingdon Drive. This was on
OL,10,FFriday 27 May 2022, just after 8pm.
OL,11,F"Officers attended, along with
OL,12,Fcolleagues from the Northern Ireland
OL,13,FAmbulance Service, and Mr Conville was
OL,14,Ftaken to hospital having sustained a
OL,15,Fserious head injury.J"Sadly, he passed
OL,16,Faway several days later, in the early
OL,17,Fhours of Monday 30 May."JDetective
OL,18,FChief Inspector McGuinness added:
OL,19,F"This physical altercation has had
OL,20,Ftragic and irreversible consequences.
OL,21,F"It has taken a young man's life and
OL,22,Fleft a loving family bereft. Their
OL,23,Fworlds have been torn apart. And,
OL,24,Fwhile I hope today's outcome offers a
OL,25,Fdegree of closure, I know they remain
OL,26,Fheartbroken.J"My thoughts, and that of
